🇭🇺 Highlights of Hungarian PM Viktor Orban’s year-end press conference

▪️ The conflict in Ukraine is precisely a special military operation since Russia never declared war on the regime in Kiev, and did not announce general mobilization;  

▪️ The European Union should not begin accession talks with Ukraine since the conflict there is ongoing;

▪️ Orban queried whether the EU intends to accept Ukraine along with the new Russian regions;

▪️ It is not in Hungary’s interests to have a border with Russia;

▪️ The launch of accession talks between the European Union and Ukraine is no more than a political gesture, and fails to bring tangible help to the citizens of that country;

▪️ Ukraine cannot be admitted to the EU without the decision of the Hungarian parliament;

▪️Orban stressed he opposed the start of accession talks with Kiev at the EU summit on December 14-15, but could not persuade the remaining 26 EU leaders to change their minds;

▪️EU member countries cannot decide to allocate financial support to Ukraine from the bloc’s budget without the consent of Hungary. They can only agree on extra-budgetary payments, as would be the case if the other 26 countries took out a common loan for this purpose;

▪️The EC has no reason to attempt to strip Hungary of its voting rights under Article 7 of the EU treaty (for violations of the rule of law), since it has just admitted that the country’s judicial system is in order;

▪️The new EU migration rules are flawed and were adopted not unanimously, but by a simple majority.

